\min_{x \in \mathbb{R}_+^K} \max \{f_1(x),f_2(x),\cdots,f_{N-1}(x)\}
 f_l(x)  = |\sum_{i \in P} x_i w^{il} |, \qquad w= e^{-j\frac{2\pi}N} 
 P \subset \{1,2,\cdots,N-1\} , \quad |P|=K 
f_1(x) = f_2(x) = \cdots = f_{N-1}(x)
 \max \{f_1(x),f_2(x),\cdots,f_{N-1}(x)\} \geq \frac1{N-1} \left(f_1(x)+f_2(x)+\cdots+f_{N-1}(x)\right) 
